div.p:
Pro:—would be viewed with less suspicion by our allies
and others concerned about increasing U.S.-
Soviet bilateralism;

Con:—would first need Soviet commitment publicly to
resist efforts to incorporate exceptions into proposal covering terrorist acts
by “national liberation groups”;

—would cause grave concern among certain member of Congress and ethnic
                    organizations who would prefer that a person fleeing the U.S.S.R. by hijacking an aircraft be prosecuted in
                    the U.S. rather than returned to the U.S.S.R.;

Con:—some states might regard Soviet involvement as
another sign of big-power interference in internal affair and react
adversely;
